Text: Linear regression needed LNotesnsf Hi Mark As per our discussion I need linear regression results equation and R and Im interested in these two cases No binning of the data Binning of the data using ms bins as done previously in which case the linear correlation I need is that on the bin average for the nacelle freestream and nacelle wind speeds As a starting point please use the spreadsheet on the transfer directory PhilippeGForMarkFisher If at all possible results before pm today would be great Sorry for the last minute notice Philippe

Data analysis needed LNotesnsf Mark Could you please analyze the data the transfer server in in the directory PhillipGForMarkFisher You have done the same type of analysis before and I have added an example of the output you provided before in the spreadsheet All I need is the mean value for the nacelle wind speed freestream wind speed and ratio of these two wind speeds for ms bins It would be great to get this by am tomorrow Thanks for your help Philippe
Re Outputdata LNotesnsf Youre right I was comparing the output example that I gave you yesterday and the previous output which are the same Thanks

Your results LNotesnsf Hi Mark Thanks for the analyses and the rapid turnaround Its great working with you Attached is your spreasheet with a couple of summary plots that you might find interesting I have included the previous results you generated for the case where no filtering on wind direction was done The results indicate to me that the additional filtering of the data is overall improving the accuracy of the freestream wind speed estimation based on the mean nacelle wind speed and mean wind speed ratio but at the cost of larger standard error because of the reduction in number of samples Therefore it seems that additional filtering might not be so valuable afterall Any comments Philippe

Re Your results LNotesnsf Thanks for your reply Mark Your observation is interesting I had not thought of that The y intercept of a linear regression can be easily set to zero in excel Its one of the trend line options Have a good weekend Philippe
